  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 11.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - He for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the lame man which was healed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V. and T.R. The words of the T.R. are thought to have crept into the text from the portions read in church beginning here, which made it necessary to supply them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Held",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; by the hand or otherwise; not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "have to",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in the spiritual sense. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The porch that is called Solomon's.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Josephus tells us that King Solomon built up with masonry only the eastern side of the temple enclosure, and that upon the artificial foundation thus formed one ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "στοά",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or covered colonnade, was built, the other sides of the temple in Solomon's time being naked and bare of buildings, but that in process of time, and by an enormous expenditure of treasure, the ground was filled up, leveled, and made firm by the masonry of huge walls all round, and then the circuit of buildings was completed. This eastern ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "στοά",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or colonnade, was called Solomon's porch (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Greatly wondering",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἔκθαμβοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", (see note on ver. 10). Acts 3:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
